column3: area-averaged changes over five regions  as simulated by CMIP6 models (individually identifiable) and CMIP5 models (blue)
These reconstructions were originally sourced from the netcdf file at https://static-content.springer.com/esm/art%3A10.1007%2Fs00382-010-0904-1/MediaObjects/382_2010_904_MOESM2_ESM.zip

Comparison between simulated annual precipitation changes and pollen-based reconstructions at the Mid-Holocene (6,000 years ago). The area-averaged changes over five regions (Iturbide et al., 2020) as simulated by CMIP6 models (individually identifiable, one ensemble member per model) and CMIP5 models (blue) are shown, stretching from the tropics to high-latitudes. All regions contain multiple quantitative reconstructions: their interquartile range are shown by boxes and with whiskers for their full range excluding outliers. (Figure adapted from Brierley et al., 2020).
Brierley et al. (2020, Climate of the Past)
Five regions include Northern Europe, Western and Central Europe, Mediterranean, Sahara/Sahel and West Africa
